                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12915428" author="pieber" created="Mon, 27 Sep 2010 18:52:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The problem was that getBytes does not include an encoding. This patch applies cleanly on master and the 1.2.x branch&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12916995" author="adamnichols" created="Fri, 1 Oct 2010 18:31:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m concerned that using ISO-8859-1 may adversely affect languages which are not Latin based (e.g. Asian character sets).  Does anyone have any files with different encodings that we can use to test?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12916999" author="pieber" created="Fri, 1 Oct 2010 18:46:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;mhm, I&apos;ve directly added ISO-8859-1 since many files are already set to this encoding (e.g. &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;).  BTW, IMHO this should not be static, but rather configurable (e.g. method overload? via the document object?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;http://svn.apache.org/repos/asf/pdfbox/trunk/pdfbox/src/main/java/org/apache/pdfbox/pdmodel/edit/PDPageContentStream.java&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://svn.apache.org/repos/asf/pdfbox/trunk/pdfbox/src/main/java/org/apache/pdfbox/pdmodel/edit/PDPageContentStream.java&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12917007" author="adamnichols" created="Fri, 1 Oct 2010 19:19:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Since ISO-8859-1 is used elsewhere, we&apos;ll keep things consistent.  I agree with Andreas that there should be some way to override this, but that will be dealt with in another task, as it&apos;s a larger change.  Committed patch in revision 1003623.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
